Description: This Les Paul Studio is in very good condition for its age. The body, neck, headstock, and hardware have some wear and tear from use. This includes scratches, dents, dings, and some cracks in the finish of the headstock. The original Tim Shaw bridge pickup has been swapped with a used Gibson 498T bridge pickup. Some of the original solder joints in the control cavity have been touched up with new solder. The six original tuners with mounting screws, tuner bushings, and washers have been swapped with used six Schaller tuners with 6 mounting screws, tuner bushings, and washers. The plastic jack plate has one minor crack near one of its mounting screws. The truss rod cover has two minor cracks near both mounting screws. The pickup selector switch plate is missing. Other than that, everything else on this guitar is 100% original.  All the electronics have been tested and are in perfect working condition. The truss rod is in perfect working condition. The guitar has been cleaned thoroughly and set up with brand new Fender Super 250 Nickel-Plated Steel Ball End Guitar Strings .09-.42. The action and intonation has been adjusted. All the strings ring clearly across the board. Free shipping to Continental U.S. or local pickup in Budd Lake, NJ (zip code: 07828)! Sold as-is! $1 starting price. No reserve.
